  "text": "The q-2q scans indicate that the as-deposited YSZ lms are textured in Fig. 2. However, Fig. 6 and 7 , u or rocking curve ). * indicates peaks from Si substrate, the 33 peak is for the forbidden 200 reflection, whereas the 61 peak is for the 400 reflection due to Cukb radiation. A summary of the variation in FWHM with growth stress (s g ) of the YSZ lms is shown in Fig. 8(b) . It shows that the FWHM of the rocking curve decrease from [CITATION_1] to 16 with growth rates ranging from 30 to 0.8 nm min À1 for (100) and (111) YSZ lms respectively. This is due to compressive stress driven annealing during growth which will discussed in detail as we go along. Thus, (100) lms are more defective than (111) lms as (100) YSZ lms show larger FWHM than (111) lms. A measure of how defective these oxide lms are can be gauged from the fact that the as-deposited rocking curve widths of epitaxial IIInitride lms on Si are routinely in the 0.1-1 range.",
